{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_36","type":"reasoning","text":"**Assessing mobile UX accessibility**\n\nIΓÇÖm looking into a potential issue with the confirmation screen back button lacking an aria-label. ThereΓÇÖs a known bug (BUG-PM-047) that covers several interactive elements missing aria-labels, but I can't report it. IΓÇÖm wondering if adding a popstate listener without cleanup could cause performance issues, though it seems there's no such issue. \n\nAlso, I'm considering if thereΓÇÖs a problem with the `handleCheckoutClick` function on Android, as it directly navigates away instead of returning to the menu."}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_37","type":"reasoning","text":"**Reviewing back button functionality**\n\nIΓÇÖm considering if the user expects a review of the back button fix only, and not the entire file. Reporting the `handleCheckoutClick` issue wouldnΓÇÖt make sense since that's already noted in known bugs. \n\nNow, there's another potential finding: even when intercepting the cart drawer state, full-screen confirmation and order-status views aren't using `pushState`. This means that navigating back from these screens on Android exits instead of returning to the menu, which is not what was intended. The current implementation uses state transitions, but lacks history push or router navigation."}}
